The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Central team
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Central team
                            
	New Delhi, Sept. 22: Senior home ministry officials will visit Karnataka tomorrow, reports our special correspondent.        
	The decision comes two days after the Centre issued a warning to the Karnataka government to check communal attacks.        
	Special secretary (internal security) Mahendra Kumawat and joint secretary (human rights) A.K. Yadav will meet the state chief secretary. They will also meet district officials of violence-hit Mangalore and Udipi.                                                                                                                                                                         
